Condition : 7 - 7. The car wash shall not operate until the following information has been submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority:
a) A topographic survey of the site;
b) A drainage plan indicating management of trade effluent on site with connections and outfall details; 
c) A cross section of the washing area with levels and flow paths;
d) Details regarding treatment of trade effluents before discharging into foul public sewer; 
e) If proposing a recycling unit, their details including specification, summary of how they work and how they can be managed;
f)  Maintenance plan and maintenance record; 
g) Explanation of the consequences of not carrying out the specified maintenance; and
h) An action plan for dealing with accidental spillages
i) details of surface water run-off from the canopy structure and where it is discharged to The use shall be carried out in accordance with the details as so agreed.

REASON: To prevent pollution of the water environment.
